1 Research Question

  • Ursprngliche Frage: Are younger people more politically competent because of greater media consumption, or despite lower political trust?

> umgendert zu: Do media consumption or political trust affect political competency differently among different age groups?

  • Problem: Political competent variable (polcmpl) only available from rounds 1-4, media variables only available from rounds 8-11 > new research question necessary

  • Erste mgliche alternative Frage: Are younger people more interested in politics because of higher media use, despite lower trust in politicians? > Outcome variable ist political interest

  • Zweite mgliche alternativeFrage: How does higher media consumption affect political trust among different age groups and what role does political interest in this? > Outcome variable ist political trust

3 Data Preparation

Filtering to rounds 8-11, recoding age group and reversing the scale for polintr (higher number = more interested)

dt_new <- dt_raw %>%
  filter(essround %in% 8:11) %>%
  mutate(
    age_group = case_when(
      agea < 30 ~ "<30",
      agea >= 30 & agea <= 59 ~ "3059",
      agea >= 60 ~ "60+"
    ))  %>%
  mutate(
    age_group = factor(age_group, levels = c("<30", "3059", "60+")),
    polintr_rev = 5 - polintr  # higher = more interested
    )

#age_group
